{"text": "REPORT DATE: 09.08.2021     FILM NUMBER:

BRAIN CT SCAN:

In the sections obtained between the base of the skull and the vertex;

The base of the skull and calvarial bone structures are within normal limits.

The fourth ventricle and basal cisterns are of normal width. Posterior fossa formations are normal.

The third ventricle is in the midline and of normal width. The lateral ventricles are normal. No displacement is detected in the midline structures of the brain.

Cerebral sulci are normal.

There is obliteration of the right cerebellar pontine angle and a mass lesion compressing the fourth ventricle with dimensions of 24x22 mm, which does not show significant calcification. The relationship of the lesion with the acoustic canal is not observed within the limits of the CT. However, the right side appears to be enlarged compared to the symmetric appearance of the acoustic canal. Evaluation is recommended in conjunction with contrast-enhanced brain MRI findings.", "report_id": 24142, "patient_no": 2009252533, "protocol_no": 21361536, "report_length": 94, "report_original": "RAPOR TARİHİ: 09.08.2021     FİLM NO:

BEYİN BT:

Kafa tabanı ve verteks arasından elde olunan kesitlerde;

Kafa kaidesi ve kalvarial kemik yapılar normal sınırlardadır.

4.ventrikül ve bazal sisternalar normal genişliktedir. Posterior fossa oluşumları olağandır.

3.ventrikül orta hatta ve normal genişliktedir. Lateral ventriküller olağandır. Beyin orta hat yapılarında yer değiştirme saptanmamıştır.

Serebral sulkuslar olağandır.

Sağ serebellar pontin köşe oblitere olup bu lokalizasyonda korteksle izodens 24x22 mm boyutlarında belirgin kalsifikasyon göstermeyen 4.ventrikülü basılayan kitle lezyonu izlenmektedir. Lezyonun akustik kanal ile ilişkisi BT sınırlarında izlenmemektedir. Ancak sağ taraf akustik kanal simetriğine oranla genişlemiş görünümdedir. Kontrastlı beyin MR bulguları eşliğinde değerlendirme önerilir.", "patient_report_count": 13}

{"text": "REPORT DATE: 19/01/2022 FILM NUMBER: 12481342

Contrastless brain CT scan;

In the evaluation of infratentorial structures, it is noteworthy that there are more prominent calcified atheroma plaques in the left vertebral artery compared to the right. There is also evidence of atrophy and folia accentuation in both cerebellar hemispheres.
In the evaluation of supratentorial structures, the presence of hyperdense appearance at the level of basal cisterns draws attention. Additionally, a high-density round nodular formation is observed in the midline axial image. The described findings surround the middle cerebral arteries. Subarachnoid hemorrhage or meningeoma surrounding the vessels were primarily considered in the differential diagnosis.
Both lateral ventricles are dilated, more prominently on the right, secondary to atrophy.
Microangiopathic changes are observed in the periventricular white matter, along with chronic lacunar infarction areas at the basal ganglionic level, mainly on the right. Additionally, there are areas of chronic infarction in the irrigation area of the right posterior cerebral artery.
At the level of the left parietal region, a slight hyperostosis causing a bony structure, believed to be associated with an 8mm calcified meningioma, is observed in the axial image of the 17th slice.
The integrity of the bone structures is normal.", "report_id": 11014, "patient_no": 2008092890, "protocol_no": 22256870, "report_length": 198, "report_original": "RAPOR TARİHİ:19/01/2022   FİLM NO:12481342

Kontrastsız     beyin   BT  tetkiki;

İnfratentorial yapıların değerlendirilmesinde her iki  vertebral arterde sol daha belirgin   kalsifik aterom plaklarının varlığı dikkati çekmektedir. Her iki serebeller hemisferde ve atrofi ve folyolarda belirginleşmenin varlığı   mevcuttur.
Supratentorial yapıların  değerlendirilmesinde  bazal sisternalar  düzeyinde hiperdens  görünümün varlığı  dikkati  çekmektedir Ayrıca orta hatta  aksiyal 23. ımajda  yüksek  dansiteli  yuvarlak   nodüler oluşum  izlenmiştir. Tarif edilen bulgular  orta serebral arterleri sarmaktadır. Ayırıcı tanıda subarak noid kanama  ya da   damarları sarmış  menenjiom öncelikle düşünülmüştür.
Her iki  lateral  ventrilül sağda daha belirgin  olmak üzere  atrofiye sekonder dilatedir. 
Periventriküler beyaz maddede mikroanjiopatik değişiklikler  ve sağda   bazal  ganglionik düzeyinde kronik   laküner infarkt  sahaları izlenmiştir.  Ayrıca  sağ PCA  sulama  sahasında   kronik infarktus alanlarının varlığı mevcuttur.
Sol parietal  düzeyde aksiyal  17. ımajda  kemik yapıda  hafif   hiperostozis sebep olan   8mm lik  kalsifiye  menenjioma ait olduğu düşünülen    görünümün varlığı dikkati çekmektedir.
Kemik yapıların bütünlüğü  normaldir.
", "patient_report_count": 4}

{"text": "REPORT DATE: 01/11/2022   FILM NO:

Unenhanced Brain CT

Both lateral ventricles, 3rd ventricle, and 4th ventricle appear wider than normal. 
From the vertex level, clear selection of secondary gray-white matter edema in cerebral sulci cannot be made in some areas.
At the level of the vertex, attention is drawn to hyperdense areas consistent with subarachnoid hemorrhage, observed within the sulcal structures extending into the periphery of the falx cerebri and at the level of the Sylvian fissures surrounding the Willis polygon.
Continuity of subarachnoid hemorrhage is also observed within the 4th ventricle.
At the level of the interventricular septum, a semi-solid area with a slight hypodense appearance measuring approximately 28x20mm is observed, which is considered to be possibly secondary to the hemorrhage shape.
In the anterior mesencephalon, an area corresponding to the level of the interpeduncular cistern, a spherical contour with a diameter of approximately 8mm is observed, which may be significant in terms of aneurysmal dilation.

In the assessment of the posterior circulation, a spherical contour with a diameter of 10x8mm, consistent with aneurysmal dilation, is observed in the location corresponding to the basilar top.
Subarachnoid hemorrhage is particularly concentrated at this level. Contrast enhancement appears normal in other vascular levels.", "report_id": 21624, "patient_no": 2008965048, "protocol_no": 23137650, "report_length": 230, "report_original": "RAPOR TARİHİ:01/11/2022   FİLM NO:

Kontrastsız beyin    BT

Her iki lateral  ventrikül ,3. ventrikül ve   4. ventrikül  normalden  geniş görünümde  izlenmektedir. 
Verteks düzeyinden   itibaren  serebral sulkuslarda  ödeme sekonder  gri beyaz cevher seçilimi   net olarak yer yer  yapılamamaktadır.
Verteks düzeyinde faks çevresinde sulkal yapılar  içine doğru uzanan her iki silviyan   fissür düzeyinde  gözlene   willis poligoni çevresinde izlenen  posteriorda interpedinküler sisternde  gözlenen subaraknoid  kanama  ile  uyumlu  hiperdens alanlar   dikkati çekmektedir. Yine 4. ventrikül   içerisinde de  subaraknoid  kanamanın   devamlılık  gösterdiği   izlenmiştir.  
İnterventriküler septum   düzeyinde  yaklaşık 28x20mm   çaplı  hafif  hipodens  görünümde  semisolid alan izlenmiştir. Kanama sekeline sekonder olabileceği düşünülmektedir. 
Mezensefalon   anteriorunda interpedinküler sistern düzeyine uyan alanda yaklaşık  8mm çaplı    sferik  konturde kanama  alanı   izlenmiş olup  bulgular   anevrizmatik  genişleme  açısından  anlamlı olabilir.  

Posterior sirkülasyon değerlendirilmesinde  baziler tepeye uyan  lokasyonda  10x8mm çaplı   sferik konturde   anevrizmatik   genişleme ile  uyumlu  görünüm izlenmektedir. 
Subaraknoid kanamanında  özellikle bu düzeyde yoğunlaştığı   gözlenmektedir.  Diğer vasküler düzeylerde  kontrastlanma olağan  görünümde izlenmektedir.", "patient_report_count": 8}

{"text": "REPORT DATE: 23.08.2022    FILM NO:12748104

Cranial CT;

The examination was performed in two phases, pre and post contrast.

Infratentorial structures are normal. There is a presence of a space-occupying lesion that is believed to be consistent with a macroadenoma, extending upwards from the suprasellar area and showing significant contrast uptake in its caudal component. The lesion measures 28mm in AP diameter, 32mm in transverse diameter, and has a cranio-caudal length of up to 48mm. The lesion has caused erosion on the dorsum sella and shows significant contrast uptake in the component progressing towards the dorsum sella. However, no significant contrast uptake is observed in the component extending into the suprasellar area. The component extending into the suprasellar area shows more peripheral ring-like contrast uptake.

It is noted that the mass lesion partially compresses the third ventricle. It is also observed that the mass lesion compresses the foramen magnum on the left side, causing displacement of the anterior communicating artery and anterior cerebral artery anteriorly and superiorly.

Furthermore, it is noted that the mass lesion completely invades the cavernous segment of the right internal carotid artery.

Lateral ventricles are within normal limits. No changes are observed in the midline structures of the brain. The nasal septum appears mildly deviated to the right.

There is a presence of mucous retention cysts in both maxillary sinuses.

The mass lesion is noted to extend posteriorly up to the prepontine cistern.

Regarding the evaluation of bony structures, no gross radiopathological findings are observed except for the lesion on the dorsum sella.", "report_id": 29234, "patient_no": 2009503577, "protocol_no": 22912594, "report_length": 193, "report_original": "RAPOR TARİHİ: 23.08.2022    FİLM NO:12748104

Kranial BT;

Tetkik pre ve post kontrast olmak üzere iki fazda elde olunmuştur. 

İnfratentorial yapılar normaldir. Suprasellar alandan yukarı doğru uzanan ve kaudal komponentinde belirgin kontrast tutulumu gösteren makroadenom ile uyumlu olduğu düşünülen yer kaplayan lezyonun varlığı mevcuttur. AP çap olarak lezyon boyutu 28mm, transvers çapı olarak 32mm ve kraniokaudal uzunluk ise 48mm ye kadar ulaşmaktadır. Lezyon dorsum sellada erozyona sebep olmuştur ve dorsum sellaya ilerleyen komponentinde belirgin kontrast tutulumu mevcuttur. Suprasellar alana uzanan komponentinde ise belirgin kontrast tutulumu izlenmemektedir. Daha çok suprasellar alana uzanan komponentinde periferik halkasal kontrast tutulumu göstermektedir. 

Kitle lezyonunun 3. ventriküle kısmen bası yaptığı dikkati çekmektedir. 3. ventriküle solda foramen magnuma bası yaptığı dikkati çekmektedir ve anterior komünikan arter ve anterior serebral arteri anterior ve superiora  doğru deplasmana sebep olmuştur. 

Ayrıca kitle lezyonun sağ internal karotis arterin kavernöz segmentini total invaze ettiği dikkati çekmiştir. 

Lateral ventrikül genişlikleri normal sınırlardadır. Beyin orta hat yapılarında yer değişikliği saptanmamıştır. Nazal septum hafifçe sağa deviye görünümdedir. 

Her iki maksiller sinüste mukus retansiyon kistlerinin varlığı mevcuttur. 

Kitle lezyonu posteriorda prepontin sisternaya kadarda uzandığı dikkati çekmektedir. 

Kemik yapıların değerlendirilmesinde dorsum sella lezyonu dışında gross radyopatolojik unsur izlenmedi. 
", "patient_report_count": 4}

{"text": "REPORT DATE: 07/02/2023   FILM NUMBER:

Contrastless brain      CT

The base of the skull and calvarial bone structures are within normal limits.
The fourth ventricle is symmetrically midline and slightly larger than normal. The cerebellopontine angle and prepontine cisterns appear dilated. Cerebellar folia are prominent. 

The third ventricle and lateral ventricles are enlarged. The third ventricle is localized midline. No displacement is observed in the midline brain structures.
The cerebral sulci and cisterns are widened.
Loss of density extending to the posterior and right tonsillar region of the right cerebellar hemisphere is observed.
Evaluation with diffusion MRG is recommended for acute ischemia.
Density loss due to chronic ischemic gliosis is observed in the periventricular white matter.

Deformation in the calvarial bone and asymmetric enlargement of the diploic space in the left frontoparietal region draw attention. A sclerotic fracture line that may be related to an old fracture and an increased density suggestive of callus formation around it are noted. Dilated vascular structures, up to 2.5mm in the widest area, are notable in the left parietal region. This appearance raises suspicion of arteriovenous malformation (AVM).

In the posterior circulation, both vertebral and basilar artery lumens are patent, without evidence of aneurysmal dilatation or critical stenosis. The right internal carotid artery is completely occluded starting from the bifurcation level. The left internal carotid artery shows a tortuous course, and there are calcified plaques that cause approximately 50% stenosis in the cavernous segment, which is the narrowest point in its intracranial segments.

{"text": "REPORT DATE: 10.08.2021    FILM NO: 12237163

In the evaluation of supratentorial structures, the presence of a 27x19mm mass lesion with hemorrhagic characteristics, surrounding edema, adjacent to the choroid plexus at the level of the right occipital horn, and in the occipitoparietal region, draws attention. In addition, a 44x35mm occupying formation with hemorrhagic characteristics, associated with compression to the right centrum semiovale and right lateral ventricle, and with significant edema, is observed cranially. Also, the presence of another 25x19mm lower density mass lesion, located at the parafalcine region, compressing the left centrum semiovale and adjacent to the corpus callosum, exerting compression on the deep white matter on the left side, is observed in axial image 16. Multiple intracranial lesions are observed in this case and are primarily consistent with metastases.

Notably, mass lesions especially compress the corpus callosum, particularly on the right side. Additionally, compression is observed at the right occipital horn of the lateral ventricle.

Minimal displacement to the left is present in the midline brain structures. The high density areas in the mass lesions are thought to be related to hemorrhagic metastases, but they may also be associated with metastatic lesions such as malignant melanoma or choriocarcinoma.

The integrity of the bone structures is within normal limits. {"text": "REPORT DATE: 11/04/2022           EXAMINATION NUMBER: 12539934

BRAIN + MAXILLOFACIAL CT

Evaluation of the brainstem in the posterior fossa was not possible due to artifacts. A high-density appearance consistent with a contusion area with approximately 16mm diameter was observed in the superior region at the level of the cerebellar vermis, as best measured in the coronal plane. In the supratentorial localization, the ventricular system and the external subarachnoid space width are generally obliterated. Widespread contusion areas with hemorrhage and findings consistent with traumatic subdural hematoma were detected bilaterally in the frontotemporoparietal region. The largest bleeding area measures approximately 25mm in diameter in the anterior section of the left temporal lobe. The ventricular system appears compressed due to the extensive edema effect. Blood values are observed at the level of the Sylvian aqueduct. Diffuse decreases in brainstem density were detected. Air values were also observed in the subdural space in the anterior section of the temporal lobe on the right, and in the anterior section of the temporal lobe on the left. Subdural hemorrhage areas are observed in the parietal on the left and in the temporoparietal on the right.

In the examination of the bone window, a fracture line was observed starting from the vertex level in the parietal and extending throughout the parietal. Additionally, a fracture line was observed at the level of the squamous part and the mastoid air cells in the temporal bone. It was seen that the fracture at the level of the mastoid air cells passed through the external auditory canal apex on the right, crossed the mastoid air cells, passed through the middle ear cavity, and extended towards the mastoid apex. It was also observed that it extended from this section to the sphenoid bone and passed through the sphenoid sinus along the sphenoid bone. A linear fracture line is also observed in the inferior section of the left temporal lobe. Compatible with bleeding, appearances were detected within the mastoid air cells and in the middle ear cavity on the right. Evaluation of the ossicular chain with temporal bone CT is recommended.

In the nasal bone, a fracture line with a slight displacement was observed in the left wing. A fracture line is also present in the right zygomatic bone. A defect of approximately 6mm was observed in the floor of the right orbit, and the downward extension of orbital fat tissue was observed from this level. The appearance may be due to an old or a new fracture. Mucosal thickening consistent with sinusitis is present in the maxillary and ethmoid sinuses, and findings consistent with hemorrhage were observed in the sphenoid sinus. Follow-up examinations are recommended for the patient.", "report_id": 27987, "patient_no": 2009468514, "protocol_no": 22436402, "report_length": 357, "report_original": "RAPOR TARİHİ: 11/04/2022            TETKİK NO: 12539934

{"text": "REPORT DATE: 26.11.2021    FILM NO: 12386441

Non-contrast Cranial CT;

The presence of hemorrhage in the prepontine cistern draws attention in the evaluation of infratentorial structures. Additionally, widespread subarachnoid hemorrhage is observed, especially on the left side, in the basal ganglia and around the Willus polygon, basal cisterns, and both Sylvian fissures. The subarachnoid hemorrhage is noted to progress towards the gyri at the level of the frontotemporal and parietal regions on the left side. The presence of asymmetrical appearance in the left Sylvian fissure draws attention, therefore, an aneurysm rupture in the left MCA trace and consequent subarachnoid hemorrhage is primarily considered in this case.

No gross radiopathology is observed in the evaluation of bone structures, but evidence of chronic sinusitis is present in the left maxillary and ethmoid sinuses.

CONCLUSION,

Subarachnoid hemorrhage is present in this case, primarily believed to be located in the left MCA origin. Contrast-free brain CT

The fourth ventricle is of normal width. Posterior fossa formations are regular. Cerebellar folia are prominent.
Mild chronic ischemic changes are present in the deep white matter.
The width of the basal cisterns and cerebral convexity sulci is slightly increased, consistent with atrophy.
Both lateral ventricles appear slightly enlarged in the context of atrophy.

Increased density consistent with contusional hemorrhage and subarachnoid hemorrhage-like densities are observed in both frontal lobes and anterior to the temporal lobes.
Increased density consistent with subarachnoid hemorrhage-like densities are also observed within the sulci in the bilateral parietotemporal region.
Subdural hematoma-like appearances are observed in both cerebral convexities, in a subarachnoid hemorrhage-like fashion, and a 5mm-thick epidural hematoma is present in the left posterior parietal region.

Density consistent with secretion is present in both maxillary sinuses, more pronounced on the left.
